  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Slice the <strong>courgette<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into quarters lengthways and then chop into large bite-size pieces</p>\r\n<p>Trim the green stalks off the<strong> aubergine<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and chop&nbsp;into large, bite-size pieces</p>\r\n<p>Cut the <strong>chestnut mushrooms</strong> into quarters (or crumble them into rough pieces)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/ratatouille-and-pesto-wheat-berries/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped courgette</strong>, <strong>aubergine</strong> and <strong>mushrooms</strong> to a baking tray (use <strong>tin foil</strong> to avoid mess!) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 20 min or until the vegetables are golden and tender</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/ratatouille-and-pesto-wheat-berries/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and roughly dice the<strong> red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 5-8 min or until beginning to soften and caramelise</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/ratatouille-and-pesto-wheat-berries/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the<strong> wheat berries</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and&nbsp;1/2<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1]</span><strong> vegetable stock cube </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)</p>\r\n<p>Cook over a high heat for 12-15 min or until tender with a slight bite</p>\r\n<p>Once cooked, drain and return to the pot and leave to cool&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/ratatouille-and-pesto-wheat-berries/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\r\n<p>Grate the <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong> finely&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Chop the<strong> basil </strong>roughly,<strong>&nbsp;</strong>including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/ratatouille-and-pesto-wheat-berries/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add the<strong> chopped garlic</strong> to the onion<strong>&nbsp;</strong>and cook for 1 min</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong>, <strong>dried&nbsp;</strong><strong>oregano</strong>, <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong>, 1 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong>, the remaining <strong>vegetable stock cube</strong> and a splash of<strong> water</strong> and cook for 4-5 min</p>\r\n<p>Once cooked, remove the <strong>softened vegetables</strong> from the oven, add them to the pan and give everything a good old mix up - this is your <strong>ratatouille </strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/ratatouille-and-pesto-wheat-berries/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, grind the <strong>chopped basil</strong>&nbsp;and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a <strong>pestle &amp; mortar </strong>to form a smooth paste</p>\r\n<p>Add 2-3 tbsp<strong> olive oil</strong> and most of the <strong>grated cheese</strong>, then&nbsp;transfer to a larger bowl</p>\r\n<p>Tip: if you don't have a pestle &amp; mortar, chop the basil leaves very finely and mix with olive oil</p>\r\n<p>Add the drained<strong> wheat berries</strong> and mix to combine - these are your <strong>pesto wheat berries</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/ratatouille-and-pesto-wheat-berries/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>ratatouille</strong> over the&nbsp;<strong>pesto wheat berries</strong></p>\r\n<p>Top with the remaining <strong>grated cheese</strong>&nbsp;and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
